                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4450: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-12T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 12, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 12—11:01 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>259. Li Yuan-hung, temporarily assuming duties of President, at Palace yesterday
                    but lives in private residence for the present. Mandate dated the 11th names W.
                    W. Yen Acting Premier. Yen countersigned mandate.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
